name=Advanced Charging Controller (ACC)
version=v2025.5.18-stable.6.3.3
versionCode=202505217
author=VR25 (community stable)
description=[community STABLE.6.3.3 -- SAFETY ROLLBACK of 6.3.2's MTK idle change. On some MediaTek kernels (e.g. Xiaomi klee/HyperOS) the current_cmd switch PASSES the quick scan check but does NOT actually hold the limit -> the battery charged past the cap (overcharge). 6.3.3: current_cmd is no longer preferred over input_suspend (which DOES stop charging); the auto-migration is removed (never move a device off a switch that is holding the limit); and a one-shot revert recovers any device 6.3.2 locked onto current_cmd back to input_suspend. KEPT the genuinely-safe input-cut resume fix (input_suspend/bypass switches resume without a reboot). Net on these phones: the limit holds (no overcharge) and charging resumes on re-plug without a reboot; true battery-idle is left off where current_cmd is unreliable (safety beats idle). Non-MediaTek devices unchanged. STABLE.6.3.2 -- MediaTek TRUE-IDLE fix. 6.3.1 added the MTK current_cmd switch but (a) it was ordered after the bare variant and (b) existing users stayed on their old LOCKED input_suspend switch because an upgrade never re-scans. On mt6375-class MTK, bare current_cmd stops charging but the system then runs off the BATTERY (discharge); true idle needs current_cmd 0 1 PLUS en_power_path 1 (keep the buck/power-path ON so the CHARGER feeds the system, battery held flat, charger stays "online" so charging resumes on its own). 6.3.2: (1) the en_power_path idle combo is now tried BEFORE the bare current_cmd; (2) a one-shot, MTK-only migration clears a stale locked input_suspend so the daemon re-scans and picks the idle switch. MTK-only, current-verified, non-MTK devices untouched; if the idle combo does not verify it falls back exactly as before. Also fixes the input_suspend no-charge-til-reboot bug (Moto & any input_suspend-only device): input_suspend cuts the input so */online reads 0 while paused, which blocked the online-gated resume forever -- the resume value is now written regardless of online for input_suspend switches (harmless unplugged, un-masks online when plugged; pause still enforces the limit so no overcharge; other switches keep the online gate). STABLE.6.3.1 -- SAFE bug-fix batch (no change to the 6.2/6.3 resume logic). MediaTek battery-IDLE is now auto-selected: the daemon tries the MTK current_cmd bypass (battery held flat, charger keeps feeding the system, charging resumes on its own) BEFORE input_suspend (which cut the input -> discharge + no-resume-til-reboot) -- fixes "discharges/disconnects at the limit" and "won't charge til reboot" on MTK/Xiaomi (e.g. klee); MTK-only, current-verified, non-MTK devices unaffected. Plus: en_power_path keeps the power path ON while paused (idle, not discharge); out-of-range numeric pause/resume in config is clamped to a safe default (a corrupted huge value could otherwise overcharge); the scheduler is leading-zero/octal-safe; and a couple of fail-safe guards on corrupted configs. STABLE.6.3 -- HOTFIX (extends 6.2 to ALL phones): the resume-after-limit fix now also covers NON-Pixel devices (Motorola/Qualcomm/etc.). Some charging switches (input_suspend, current_max=0, charging_enabled=0) hold their "off" state across an unplug/replug, so after the limit was hit, re-plugging did nothing until the battery fell to the resume level -- or, on switches that latch, until a reboot (the reported Motorola symptom: stops correctly at the limit, then will not resume on re-plug). On a genuine plug-in below your limit, ACC now re-arms the switch immediately (generic_rearm), so charging resumes without a reboot. One-shot per plug (no sawtooth), skipped on the boot loop (respects off_mid_charge), Pixel/Tensor keep using the native_unlatch path from 6.2. STABLE.6.2 -- HOTFIX: Pixel/Tensor charging now RESUMES after the limit without a reboot. rc20's native firmware mode (charge_stop_level + charge_start_level) trusted the Tensor driver to resume on its own, but that driver LATCHES "stopped" and ignores charge_start_level (an upstream Google bug, reproduced on Pixel 6..10 and even with no ACC installed) -- so once your limit was hit, re-plugging did nothing and only a reboot restored charging. The daemon now detects the latched state (plugged in, at/below your resume level, or a fresh plug-in below the limit, while the kernel still reports not-charging) and briefly pulses charge_stop_level=100 -- the only value that re-arms the FET -- then immediately restores your real stop level, so there is no overshoot. It self-disables on phones whose firmware already resumes correctly, never fires inside the [resume..limit] idle band (no sawtooth), and only ever lets the cell charge toward the limit ACC still enforces (cannot overcharge). Non-Pixel devices are unaffected (native mode only runs on google,charger hardware). STABLE.6 -- `acca --state` state export, fixed to report the real acc version + a derived charging status + an always-fresh snapshot (rc1 showed empty version, unknown status, and a frozen timestamp). Additive; no charging-behavior change. Includes all STABLE.5 fixes: restored default max_temp to 50C -- stable.4's "gentler 45C" collapsed cooldown_temp and max_temp onto the same value (45 45), which disables the cooldown cycle (it breaks the instant it would start). The sane band is cooldown 45 < max 50 (resume 40, shutdown 55); existing 45/45 configs auto-repair once, no command. ACC is fully STANDALONE (uninstalling the AccA app never removes it -- it is a normal module with its own persistent config); AccA boot receiver registered. Charges to your limit, stops, resumes at your resume level -- a tight cycle in your range. Existing configs auto-migrate, no command. on Pixel/Tensor, no overshoot (driven by the target level on both sides, never "charge to 100 then interrupt"); default discharges down to the limit then HOLDS there (battery-idle), or cycles to the lower limit when idle is off; allow_idle_above_pcap defaults false (never sit above the limit); settings apply within ~1s; daemon survives front-end restarts; fail-safe on every capacity/temp limit + breach watchdog; scanner can LOCK a chosen method. fix9: full fail-safe coverage + flat-hold on all charge-limit nodes + breach watchdog. fix8: malformed-config fail-safe + locked-switch recovery. fix7: Pixel/Tensor cap now HOLDS at the limit. Drives the google charge_stop_level node to pause_capacity so the firmware holds the battery flat at the cap (tight, no overshoot, true idle) instead of toggling 100/5 and sawtoothing past it; switch scanner prefers idle/flat-hold switches; restores retry-on-stall (no daemon re-init mid-pause). Includes fix2-fix6.] Extend your battery's service life by controlling charging current, temperature, and voltage. Any root solution is supported. The installation is always "systemless". Works on Android and KaiOS.
updateJson=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/VR-25/acc/master/module.json
